## Security Fixes Summary

All critical/high vulnerabilities have been fixed. Here's what was implemented:

### ✅ 1. JWT Signing Method Validation
**Status**: Already secure, verified in `internal/auth/jwt/jwt.go:137-141`
- Explicit HMAC type checking: `if _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodHMAC); !ok`
- Uses `jwt.WithValidMethods([]string{"HS256"})` for algorithm whitelisting

### ✅ 2. Rate Limiting on Auth Endpoints
**Fixed in**: `services/auth-service/main.go:119-150`
- Applied strict rate limiting (10 req/min) to sensitive endpoints: `/auth/login`, `/auth/register`, `/auth/refresh`, `/auth/oidc/`, `/auth/saml/acs`
- Applied general rate limiting (60 req/min) to all other endpoints
- Uses IP-based tracking with automatic cleanup

### ✅ 3. SAML XML Parser XXE Protection
**Fixed in**: `internal/auth/saml/saml.go`
- Added `validateXMLSecurity()` function with explicit XXE pattern detection
- Blocks: `<!ENTITY`, `<!DOCTYPE`, `<xi:include`, `xpointer:`, and dangerous URL schemes
- Added SSRF protection in `loadMetadata()` - rejects private network IPs
- Enforces 10MB max XML size

### ✅ 4. OIDC State Parameter Expiration
**Status**: Already secure in `internal/auth/oidc/oidc.go:237-240`
- State expires after 10 minutes
- Uses `sync.Map` for concurrent-safe storage

### ✅ 5. Database Query Parameterization
**Status**: All queries use parameterized statements
- Verified in `services/auth-service/repository/user.go`
- All queries use `$1`, `$2`... placeholders with pgx

### ✅ 6. Additional Security Enhancements
**Fixed in**: Multiple files

| File | Enhancement |
|------|-------------|
| `services/auth-service/main.go` | Fixed inconsistent JWT secret validation (now requires 32 chars) |
| `internal/shared/middleware/auth.go` | Added CSP, COOP, COOP headers to SecurityHeadersMiddleware |
| `services/auth-service/handler/login.go` | Added 1MB request body limit, input validation |
| `services/auth-service/handler/register.go` | Added input length limits, control character detection |

### Test Results
- ✅ Build succeeds: `go build ./...`
- ✅ Unit tests pass: `go test ./internal/auth/... ./internal/shared/...`
- ✅ `go vet ./...` passes with no warnings
